V38.5
*****

   @{b}*@{ub} Quirk Fix: Uppercase GadgetKeys() now are converted to lowercase for them
     to work correctly.  Found by Michael Barsoom.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: Fixed a mean bug in the library task code which could cause
     serious problems when the same task opens the library twice. Bug found by
     Janne Jalkanen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Work arround: BGUI should not have any problems with hacks like MagicMenu
     and CycleToMenu anymore. Included some additional code from Osma
     Ahvenlampi's "NewObtainGIRPort" patch to the library.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: Replace a couple of NULLs by NIL in the E macros.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: Fixed some font related problems with the cycle gadget.
     Sometimes the font height was computed wrong.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: In some rare occasions the keyboard handling of objects could
     get caught in a loop.  Should not happen anymore.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: The windowclass did not fall back to topaz 8 or the specified
     font anymore! Fixing this bug also shed light on another bug in the
     layout engine. Both bugs fixed. Bug found by Nick Christie.

   @{b}*@{ub} Quirk fix. It was not possible to add tab-cycle string objects to a
     window object in stages.  Now it is. Found by Paul Weterings.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: Adding the first item to a listview did not show on the screen.
     Bug found by Emmanuel Doguet.

   @{b}*@{ub} The rastport pointer passed to the Listview custom rendering hook is
     cached now.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: Removed a rendering bug in the MX class which screwed up visuals
     a bit when the object was switched from disabled to enabled state. This
     was true for the normal MX objects and mx objects in tabs mode. Bug found
     by Janne Jalkanen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added some defines to fix a spelling error in the BGUI headers in which
     "Separator" was misspelled as "Seperator". Reported by Nick Christie.

   @{b}*@{ub} BUG FIX: The minimum height of string object with a label was bigger than
     string objects without a label. Bug found by Emmanuel Doguet.

   @{b}*@{ub} Released as bug-fix patch on the mailing list.


@EndNode

